   <body>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Lift the load carefully and tilt the mast back a short distance. </p>
            <p>
               <p>
                  <fig id="fig_khv_dyy_5gc">
                     <image href="media/image789.png" id="image_mhv_dyy_5gc" placement="inline"/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
               <p>Typical Example</p>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Tilt the mast further back to cradle the load </p>
            <p>
               <p>
                  <fig id="fig_e1g_2yy_5gc">
                     <image href="media/image790.png" id="image_g1g_2yy_5gc" placement="inline"/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
               <p>Typical Example</p>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Operate the lift truck in reverse until the load is clear of
the other material.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Lower the cradled load to the travel position.</p>
            <p>
               <note id="note_thh_fyy_5gc" type="note">
                  <p>Lift and tilt speeds are controlled by engine rpm.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </li>
      </ol>
